The paper deals with a graph problem, specifically the Independent Feedback Vertex Set (IFVS) problem, which is a well-studied problem in graph theory. The algorithmic approach used in the paper involves parameterization, which is a common technique used in computational complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem is also related to graph theory and combinatorics, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as likely sub-categories. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
